  "name": "Magic in Motion",
  "type": "spell",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You invoke the imagery of magical elements and your catalysts bring your idea to a quick, violent life. Choose fire, electricity, or cold. You expend an ephemeral catalyst and launch a projectile of your chosen element at a target within 30 feet of you. Make a spell attack. On a hit, a target takes @Damage[1d6+1|] damage plus your attribute modifier, or double on a critical hit. The damage type is of the type you selected, and this spell gains that trait.</p><p>You can choose to eschew the ephemeral catalyst cost by spending a focus point instead. If you do, you cast this spell with 2 actions but the range of this spell increases to 60 feet and deals @Damage[3d6] damage instead (doubled on a critical hit).</p><hr /><p><strong>Heightened (3rd)</strong> The damage of the cantrip increases to 2d6+2 plus your modifier, or 6d6 if you use a focus point.</p><p><strong>Heightened (6th)</strong> The damage of the cantrip increases to 3d6+3 plus your modifier, or 12d6 if you use a focus point.</p><p><strong>Heightened (9th)</strong> The damage of the cantrip increases to 4d6+4 plus your modifier, or 18d6 if you use a focus point.</p>"
    },
